- The top 5 neighborhoods are determined by combining the rankings of average price per square foot and average days on market, with lower rankings indicating better performance in these categories; 
- Average price per square foot is an indicator of the neighborhood's property value, while average days on market is an indicator of the neighborhood's market demand; 
- By considering both factors, the query aims to identify neighborhoods that are not only expensive but also in high demand.
